{
  "texts": [
    "If two content tags (words) A and B occur on similar (but not necessarily the same) films sharing other tags (context), then A and B are likely similar in content description (meaning or function).",
    "The method transfer of distributional approaches from text applications to other data types has previously also proven useful in other fields, e.g.",
    "science of science [94] and social network analysis [95].",
    "Since the number of unique content tags and the amount of film data are fairly small (in NLP terms), we use a simple model with few hyperparameters, Latent Semantic Analysis [96].",
    "It consists of weighting the co-occurrence count matrix of the content tags (we use Positive Point-wise Mutual Information), followed by Singular Value Decomposition."
  ]
}